The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, January 12, 2003  Fine Print				 				 				 																Beautiful moment																																	 Los Angeles, Jan. 11 (AP): Academy award-winning actress Jennifer Connelly has married A Beautiful Mind co-star Paul Bettany, her agent has said.																																	Connelly, who won a best supporting actress Oscar last year for playing the wife of schizophrenic math genius John Forbes Nash in the film, exchanged vows with Bettany during a private ceremony in Scotland over the holidays.																						Her agent, Risa Shapiro, said yesterday she could not offer any specifics about the event.																																	Bettany, who has also appeared as 14th century writer Geoffrey Chaucer in A Knights Tale, played Nashs mysterious classmate in A Beautiful Mind.																																	Connelly made her screen debut as a child in 1984s Once Upon a Time in America and has appeared in the films The Rocketee, Dark City, Waking the Dead, Pollock and the upcomig comic-book adaptation of The Hulk. 
